296
00:11:47,604 --> 00:11:49,314
He doesn't even want
to be seen with me.

297
00:11:49,439 --> 00:11:50,501
So started to wonder

298
00:11:50,774 --> 00:11:52,962
if maybe I'm imagining
all the good stuff.

299
00:11:53,128 --> 00:11:55,954
Jenna plus and I might have
been from different planets,

300
00:11:56,079 --> 00:11:58,426
but her Matty heartbreak
was the same.

301
00:11:58,592 --> 00:12:01,220
[Cell phone tune]

302
00:12:01,386 --> 00:12:02,430
There it was.

303
00:12:02,596 --> 00:12:05,016
The answer I was chasing.

304
00:12:05,182 --> 00:12:07,366
I couldn't live in the safety
of denial anymore.

305
00:12:07,491 --> 00:12:09,979
She was with Matty.
He was with her.

306
00:12:10,145 --> 00:12:11,439
And I was with cancer.

307
00:12:11,605 --> 00:12:14,373
I'm gonna let him sweat it
for a little while.

308
00:12:14,498 --> 00:12:16,653
Thanks for listening.

309
00:12:18,070 --> 00:12:19,197
Are you okay?

310
00:12:19,363 --> 00:12:21,713
Whatever the misunderstanding
was today,

311
00:12:21,838 --> 00:12:23,159
it'll blow over.

312
00:12:23,325 --> 00:12:25,203
Nothing's ever as bad as it seems.

313
00:12:25,369 --> 00:12:26,663
Here.

314
00:12:26,829 --> 00:12:29,749
Take my last smoke.
I'm gonna grab another pack.

315
00:12:29,915 --> 00:12:32,057
As much as I wanted
to hate on Jenna plus,

316
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:33,158
I couldn't.

317
00:12:33,283 --> 00:12:34,193
The bitch was decent.

318
00:12:34,461 --> 00:12:36,195
Maybe even sweet.

319
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:39,020
And it made me
really want to kill myself.

320
00:12:43,387 --> 00:12:44,798
{pub}I didn't know
you were a smoker.

321
00:12:44,923 --> 00:12:46,224
I'm not.

322
00:12:46,391 --> 00:12:48,935
Well, I hear lung cancer
does make your ass look huge.

323
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:51,104
Well, I'm having a crappy day.

324
00:12:51,229 --> 00:12:52,939
Everyone thinks
I tried to kill myself,

325
00:12:53,064 --> 00:12:54,574
and there's a lame guy
selling T-shirts

326
00:12:54,699 --> 00:12:55,817
keeping the stupid story alive.

327
00:12:55,983 --> 00:12:58,236
I don't think
you tried to kill yourself.

328
00:12:58,403 --> 00:12:59,779
- Really?
- No.

329
00:12:59,945 --> 00:13:01,239
You're not the type.

330
00:13:01,405 --> 00:13:04,117
Well, unless you keep smoking.

331
00:13:08,662 --> 00:13:09,622
And there's a guy...

332
00:13:09,788 --> 00:13:11,165
Oh. Mysterious.

333
00:13:11,331 --> 00:13:12,500
I really like him,
but he has a girlfriend.

334
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:13,835
Who is it?

335
00:13:14,001 --> 00:13:15,211
I can't say.

336
00:13:15,377 --> 00:13:16,421
Oh. So I'd know him.

337
00:13:16,587 --> 00:13:18,047
No comment.

338
00:13:18,213 --> 00:13:19,833
Aw, come on.

339
00:13:19,958 --> 00:13:22,736
Does this guy even know
that you like him?

340
00:13:22,861 --> 00:13:25,012
I'd say it's pretty clear.

341
00:13:25,178 --> 00:13:28,141
I mean...
He's funny and he's cool,

342
00:13:28,266 --> 00:13:29,809
and everybody likes him,

343
00:13:29,975 --> 00:13:31,344
which is part of the problem.

344
00:13:31,469 --> 00:13:33,479
But I feel like I see
who he really is,

345
00:13:33,645 --> 00:13:34,447
and he gets me.

346
00:13:34,572 --> 00:13:36,232
Yeah.

347
00:13:36,398 --> 00:13:37,517
But we're not
on the same level,

348
00:13:37,642 --> 00:13:39,619
and he can never be
with a freak like me, so...

349
00:13:39,744 --> 00:13:40,945
It's kinda hopeless.

350
00:13:41,111 --> 00:13:43,890
Maybe you're misjudging
the situation,

351
00:13:44,015 --> 00:13:45,325
and this guy really does like you...

352
00:13:45,450 --> 00:13:48,161
Just the way you are.

353
00:13:49,661 --> 00:13:50,830
Naptime's almost over.

354
00:13:58,211 --> 00:13:59,172
[Door slams]

355
00:14:00,497 --> 00:14:02,633
Good day today!

356
00:14:02,799 --> 00:14:05,470
I snuck by earlier

357
00:14:05,636 --> 00:14:08,014
and checked on your progress,

358
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:10,516
and you were all busy working away.

359
00:14:10,682 --> 00:14:12,602
As always, I appreciate your respect

360
00:14:12,768 --> 00:14:14,562
of the honor system.

361
00:14:14,728 --> 00:14:17,557
You make my job a pleasure.

362
00:14:17,682 --> 00:14:19,782
You're all dismissed.

363
00:14:21,443 --> 00:14:23,063
Hey, mom, it's me.

364
00:14:23,188 --> 00:14:26,073
Uh...When your tan is dry,
come pick me up.

365
00:14:26,239 --> 00:14:28,493
Jenna.

366
00:14:28,659 --> 00:14:32,747
I, um...
I just wanted to say I, uh...

367
00:14:32,913 --> 00:14:34,808
Okay.

368
00:14:34,933 --> 00:14:36,042
You know that guy that
we were talking about?

369
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:37,777
Yes.

370
00:14:37,902 --> 00:14:39,613
Um, I just want to throw in
my two cents

371
00:14:39,738 --> 00:14:41,422
and say that I'm sure
you're on his radar.

372
00:14:41,588 --> 00:14:43,650
I mean, he'd be lucky--

373
00:14:43,775 --> 00:14:46,803
well, I--I mean, anyone would be
lucky to be with you.

374
00:14:46,969 --> 00:14:49,723
Well, thank you
for the pity party.

375
00:14:49,848 --> 00:14:51,157
But I think I'll live.

376
00:14:51,282 --> 00:14:53,100
The T-shirts say so.

377
00:14:53,266 --> 00:14:55,295
[Chuckles]

378
00:14:55,420 --> 00:14:57,831
No, um, seriously.

379
00:14:57,956 --> 00:15:01,134
I'll bet you anything if this
guy didn't have a girlfriend

380
00:15:01,259 --> 00:15:03,236
that he'd be all over you.

381
00:15:03,402 --> 00:15:05,196
- Would he now?
- Yeah.

382
00:15:05,362 --> 00:15:07,114
He would.

383
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:08,574
It was nice to hear.

384
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:11,077
If Jake could see me
in a positive light,

385
00:15:11,243 --> 00:15:12,412
maybe other people could too.

386
00:15:12,537 --> 00:15:13,704
Thank you.

387
00:15:27,634 --> 00:15:29,178
Don't stop on account of me.

388
00:15:40,050 --> 00:15:40,927
She's acting out.

389
00:15:41,052 --> 00:15:42,428
We gave her too much rope.

390
00:15:42,553 --> 00:15:43,429
She's never had detention before.

391
00:15:43,554 --> 00:15:45,403
There have to be consequences.

392
00:15:45,569 --> 00:15:46,432
Isn't detention a consequence?

393
00:15:46,557 --> 00:15:49,302
She needs parental
punishing too.

394
00:15:49,427 --> 00:15:50,533
But nothing too harsh.

395
00:15:50,699 --> 00:15:51,771
What do you think?

396
00:15:51,896 --> 00:15:52,994
Should we send her to bed
without dessert?

397
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:54,340
So that she wakes up skinnier?

398
00:15:54,465 --> 00:15:55,841
No, that's not a punishment,
that's a reward.

399
00:15:55,966 --> 00:16:00,167
We can't let her think
we're taking this lightly.

400
00:16:00,333 --> 00:16:03,282
How do we do this?

401
00:16:03,407 --> 00:16:06,308
We start by presenting
a unified front.

402
00:16:08,675 --> 00:16:12,081
Your behavior at school today
was unacceptable.

403
00:16:12,675 --> 00:16:16,338
Getting physical with someone
is never the answer.

404
00:16:17,154 --> 00:16:18,519
We're...

405
00:16:20,228 --> 00:16:22,231
disappointed in you.

406
00:16:22,397 --> 00:16:23,369
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to flip out.

407
00:16:23,494 --> 00:16:25,004
I was just trying
to stand up for myself.

408
00:16:25,129 --> 00:16:26,444
I mean, mom told me
to take more risks.

409
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,821
You told her
to take more risks?

410
00:16:28,987 --> 00:16:31,157
In the context
of what she was wearing.

411
00:16:31,323 --> 00:16:33,346
What does that even mean?

412
00:16:33,471 --> 00:16:36,829
I told her to wear
a shirt without a bra.

413
00:16:36,995 --> 00:16:38,789
Why would you tell her that?

414
00:16:38,955 --> 00:16:40,458
Our daughter is 15!

415
00:16:40,624 --> 00:16:41,792
She doesn't need to skip the bra!

416
00:16:41,958 --> 00:16:43,122
It was a backless shirt!

417
00:16:43,247 --> 00:16:44,587
Do you guys want me
to come back in ten minutes?

418
00:16:44,753 --> 00:16:45,796
Both: 15!

419
00:16:51,843 --> 00:16:55,434
Everything that once was
simple was now complicated.

420
00:16:55,559 --> 00:16:57,236
Matty's best friend had kissed me.

421
00:16:57,361 --> 00:16:59,538
And Matty didn't want me
to be his girlfriend.

422
00:16:59,663 --> 00:17:01,140
'Cause he already had one.

423
00:17:01,265 --> 00:17:03,676
And no matter how much I wanted
her to disappear,

424
00:17:03,801 --> 00:17:04,910
she wouldn't.

425
00:17:05,035 --> 00:17:06,779
She was real and she had a name.

426
00:17:06,904 --> 00:17:08,361
Olivia.

427
00:17:08,527 --> 00:17:10,349
As expected,
it was prettier than mine.

428
00:17:10,474 --> 00:17:12,323
[Cell phone tune]

429
00:17:13,511 --> 00:17:15,988
So how was juvie?

430
00:17:16,113 --> 00:17:18,124
Nothing like I thought
it would be.

431
00:17:18,249 --> 00:17:20,059
That's pretty much
the theme of the day.

432
00:17:20,184 --> 00:17:21,540
Brace yourself, J.

433
00:17:21,706 --> 00:17:23,084
I CSI'd your barnacle.

434
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:25,053
Check out his page.

435
00:17:28,588 --> 00:17:30,603
You're not the object
of his affection.

436
00:17:30,728 --> 00:17:33,672
See, his hand is on
miss Burndahl's knee.

437
00:17:33,797 --> 00:17:35,388
Um, hurl.

438
00:17:35,554 --> 00:17:36,475
[Sighs]

439
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:37,765
He is an office aid.

440
00:17:37,931 --> 00:17:40,679
I am such a jerk.

441
00:17:40,804 --> 00:17:43,771
Kyle's not a stalker,
Jenna plus is nice.

442
00:17:43,937 --> 00:17:45,815
What'next?

443
00:17:45,981 --> 00:17:47,386
So you attacked
an innocent office aid.

444
00:17:47,511 --> 00:17:49,402
We're all spun out on the crazy car.

445
00:17:49,568 --> 00:17:50,923
It happens to the best of us.

446
00:17:51,048 --> 00:17:53,239
I mean, I shame-spiral, like, weekly.

447
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:54,490
No bigs.

448
00:17:54,656 --> 00:17:56,409
Call me if you want to ugly-cry.

449
00:17:58,660 --> 00:17:59,745
[Sighs]

450
00:17:59,911 --> 00:18:03,235
Turns out I had been smoking
the emotional crack pipe

451
00:18:03,360 --> 00:18:07,039
and I needed to take a drastic
12 steps back to recovery.

452
00:18:07,164 --> 00:18:09,475
I had already acknowledged
I had a problem.

453
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:11,677
So I decided to skip the middle steps

454
00:18:11,802 --> 00:18:13,092
and go straight to number nine--

455
00:18:13,258 --> 00:18:15,219
making amends.

456
00:18:15,385 --> 00:18:17,216
I'm not wearing the shirt!

457
00:18:17,341 --> 00:18:19,181
I know! I'm sorry!

458
00:18:19,347 --> 00:18:21,153
Listen, I made a huge mistake

459
00:18:21,278 --> 00:18:22,601
calling you out in front of everyone.

460
00:18:22,767 --> 00:18:24,395
You're surprisingly strong.

461
00:18:24,561 --> 00:18:26,692
I feel really bad
about all of this,

462
00:18:26,817 --> 00:18:28,232
and I'd like to make it up to you.

463
00:18:28,398 --> 00:18:29,984
Can I buy a shirt
to support your band?

464
00:18:32,027 --> 00:18:32,865
You can just have it.

465
00:18:32,990 --> 00:18:35,281
No, let me pay for it,
I insist.

466
00:18:37,407 --> 00:18:38,471
This whole thing is just ridiculous.

467
00:18:38,596 --> 00:18:40,619
I mean, I just kept
seeing you everywhere.

468
00:18:40,785 --> 00:18:43,581
And I thought you were a... creeper.

469
00:18:43,747 --> 00:18:45,082
Turns out, I am.

470
00:18:45,248 --> 00:18:47,251
Okay.

471
00:18:47,417 --> 00:18:48,981
We cool?

472
00:18:49,106 --> 00:18:50,546
Yeah.

473
00:18:54,411 --> 00:18:57,490
You should hear my band
play sometime.

474
00:18:57,615 --> 00:18:58,846
We kill it.

475
00:18:59,012 --> 00:19:01,766
Yeah, I'd love to.

476
00:19:03,586 --> 00:19:05,436
[Hinges squeak]

477
00:19:05,602 --> 00:19:08,731
[Comically ominous music]

478
00:19:08,897 --> 00:19:11,358
♪ ♪

479
00:19:15,111 --> 00:19:17,615
Come sit with me!

480
00:19:24,374 --> 00:19:25,351
Cool specs.

481
00:19:25,476 --> 00:19:26,719
They're not real or anything.

482
00:19:26,844 --> 00:19:28,959
I like to wear them so that
people take me seriously.

483
00:19:29,125 --> 00:19:31,457
Funny, even Jenna plus
was concerned

484
00:19:31,582 --> 00:19:32,971
with how people perceived her.

485
00:19:34,631 --> 00:19:36,759
I didn't know you two
knew each other.

486
00:19:36,925 --> 00:19:37,760
Busted.

487
00:19:37,926 --> 00:19:40,387
We're detention buddies.

488
00:19:40,553 --> 00:19:42,598
I need ranch.

489
00:19:42,764 --> 00:19:45,810
You don't seem like the type
that would be in detention.

490
00:19:45,976 --> 00:19:48,562
Maybe you don't know
what type I am.

491
00:19:48,728 --> 00:19:51,110
So, um...

492
00:19:51,235 --> 00:19:52,900
How do you guys know each other?

493
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:54,780
Who, Liv?

494
00:19:54,905 --> 00:19:58,948
She's kinda my girlfriend.

495
00:19:59,114 --> 00:20:00,407
In-law.

496
00:20:00,573 --> 00:20:03,088
She and my brother have been
off and on for a while.

497
00:20:03,213 --> 00:20:06,458
I don't really know what's going on.

498
00:20:11,543 --> 00:20:12,878
Weird.

499
00:20:13,044 --> 00:20:15,381
So you two kinda look alike.

500
00:20:15,547 --> 00:20:17,503
[Laughs]

501
00:20:17,628 --> 00:20:18,571
Yeah.

502
00:20:18,696 --> 00:20:21,220
Nah, she's way prettier
than me.

503
00:20:21,386 --> 00:20:22,975
It was our first lunch
together.

504
00:20:23,100 --> 00:20:26,045
And I realized it wasn't
my stigma or another girl

505
00:20:26,170 --> 00:20:28,347
keeping me from Matty.

506
00:20:28,472 --> 00:20:30,605
It was how I saw myself.

507
00:20:32,814 --> 00:20:33,819
Next on <i>Awkward.</i>

508
00:20:33,944 --> 00:20:34,753
You know this is
a charity <i>league.</i>

509
00:20:34,878 --> 00:20:36,527
Not a charity, right?

510
00:20:36,693 --> 00:20:37,823
We are gonna rock
the knick knackers.

511
00:20:37,948 --> 00:20:38,821
We are!

512
00:20:38,987 --> 00:20:41,991
You have to be cruel
to be kind.

513
00:20:42,157 --> 00:20:43,325
Both: Sadie wrote the letter!

514
00:20:43,491 --> 00:20:44,827
Do you think Matty
knows Jake kissed me?

515
00:20:44,993 --> 00:20:46,412
No way.
Guys don't talk.

